               <msContents defective="false">
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1" defective="false">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist, his baptismal name Krǝstos ʾAbuhu (e.g. fol. 9ra) and names of his parents Yǝrdǝʿannä ʾƎgziʾ and Märkeza (e.g. fol. 6vb); names of other saints like Qirqos (e.g. fol. 7ra), ʾAmanuʾel (e.g. fol. 9va), Gäbrä Nazrawi (e.g. fol. 12vb), Giyorgis (e.g. fol. 26vb); Mäṭaʿ (fol. 41rb), Libanos (fol. 41va); names of the donors.  &#xD;
A few lines in the incipit page of Text I, incipit of Texts II-V, incipits of the sections of all texts.&#xD;
A few words like Mänfäs Qǝddus "Holy Spirit", ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer "God", Śǝllase "Trinity", Ṗäraqliṭos "Paraclete"; words sǝmʿu "listen!" (fol. 40rb) and wä-halläwa "they existed" (fol. 41rb) and the word sälam.&#xD;
Elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
